thumb|1880 illustration depicting eustace bright telling stories to several children in a wonder - book for girls and boys a wonder - book for girls and boys ( 1851 ) is a children 's book written by american author nathaniel hawthorne in which he rewrites myths from greek mythology .

american literature : he wrote " a wonder - book for girls and boys " to capitalize on the success of " the scarlet letter "

